urlText: City Circle: Trains run in one direction only, from Central first stop Museum
content:
Saturday 12 and Sunday 13 September
  • Trains run around the City Circle in one direction only, from Central first stop Museum.
  • Some trains start or end at Central.
  • You may need to change trains to continue your journey.
  • If you are travelling to Circular Quay from Town Hall or Wynyard you can catch the light rail.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
You may also be affected by trackwork if you are travelling to Sydney Airport
  • If you are travelling to Sydney International Airport or Domestic Airport, please change at Town Hall, Central or Redfern for a T4 Eastern Suburbs & Illawarra Line train to Wolli Creek, then change for a T8 Airport & South Line train.
subtitle: City Circle: Trains run in one direction only, from Central first stop Museum

urlText: Trackwork may affect your travel
content:
Saturday 12 and Sunday 13 September
  • Trackwork on the City Circle, T3 Bankstown and T8 Airport & South lines may affect how you travel.
  • All Cronulla and some Waterfall trains make extra stops at St Peters and Erskineville.

urlText: Trackwork may affect your travel
content:

  • Trains run from Macarthur or Revesby to the City via the Airport, in that direction only.
  • Trains from the City to Revesby or Macarthur run via Sydenham.

  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

urlText: Trackwork between Newcastle Interchange and Broadmeadow
content:
Monday 7 to Thursday 10 September
  • Nightly from 9.40pm until 2.40am, buses replace trains from Broadmeadow to Newcastle Interchange.
  • Trains run to the normal timetable from Hunter Line stations to Waratah then end at Broadmeadow.
  • Nightly from 10.15pm until 12.30am, buses replace the 22:18, 23:18 and 00:18 trains from Newcastle Interchange to Waratah.
  • These trains run to the normal timetable from Waratah to Hunter Line stations.
  • On Tuesday and Wednesday morning, buses replace the 03:18 and 03:36 trains from Newcastle Interchange to Broadmeadow. These trains start from Broadmeadow and run to the normal timetable from Waratah to Scone or Telarah. On Thursday morning these trains leave Newcastle Interchange as normal.
  • Buses from Newcastle Interchange leave up to 15 minutes earlier than the normal train timetable.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes

1AHU: Newcastle Interchange then all stations to Waratah - one direction only
22HU: Broadmeadow then Waratah - one direction only
60CN: Broadmeadow, Hamilton, Newcastle Interchange and return
subtitle: Trackwork between Newcastle Interchange and Broadmeadow

properties.speechText:

    Nightly from 9 40 p m until 2 40 a m, buses replace trains from Broadmeadow to Newcastle Interchange.
    Trains run to the normal timetable from Hunter Line stations to Waratah then end at Broadmeadow.
    Nightly from 10 15 p m until 12 30 a m, buses replace some trains from Newcastle Interchange to Waratah.
    These trains run to the normal timetable from Waratah to Hunter Line stations.
    On Tuesday and Wednesday morning, buses replace the 03:18 and 03:36 trains from Newcastle Interchange to Broadmeadow. These trains start from Broadmeadow and run to the normal timetable from Waratah to Scone or Telarah. On Thursday morning these trains leave Newcastle Interchange as normal.
